A '''Finnophone''' is someone that speaks the [[Finnish language]] either natively or by adoption. As an adjective, the word means "Finnish-speaking." There are an estimated six million Finnophones world-wide, most of them living in [[Finland]], where the language originates. Smaller Finnophone communities also exist in neighbouring [[Sweden]], [[Norway]], [[Russia]] and [[Estonia]].

